From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: aiopquic <noreply@aiopquic>
Date: Tue, 27 May 2026 15:30:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] picoquic_mark_active_stream: NULL ctx means "do not change"

picoquic_mark_active_stream unconditionally assigns
stream->app_stream_ctx = app_stream_ctx in its happy path. When an
app calls it with NULL, this CLOBBERS any app_stream_ctx that was
previously set via picoquic_set_app_stream_ctx (e.g. by a layered
stack like h3zero/picowt).

This is a problem in any layered stack where one layer sets
app_stream_ctx for its own bookkeeping (h3zero stores its per-stream
ctx there) and a different layer above calls mark_active_stream
without an opinion on the ctx (a pull-model app pulling bytes via
prepare_to_send doesn't need to set a ctx; it just wants to wake the
worker). The bookkeeping layer's pointer is silently zeroed; the
per-stream retirement callback (picoquic_callback_stream_released,
patch 0003) then fires with app_stream_ctx == NULL and the app
cannot route the signal back to its per-stream state.

Concrete repro: aiopquic's WT sender path (push_stream_data ->
SPSC_EVT_TX_MARK_ACTIVE -> mark_active_stream(.., NULL)) clobbers
h3zero's stream_ctx. On FIN-ack the stream_released callback's
`app_stream_ctx != NULL` guard fails and h3zero never learns the
stream is retired -- sender-side per-stream state accumulates for
the full session lifetime.

Fix: treat NULL as "do not change" in both is_active branches.
Callers that genuinely want to clear app_stream_ctx have
picoquic_unlink_app_stream_ctx, which is unambiguous about intent.
Documented behaviour of mark_active_stream (picoquic.h:1373) does
not specify NULL semantics so this is not a documented-behaviour
change.

NOTE: deliberately does NOT modify picoquic_add_to_stream_with_ctx
(same clobber pattern). Its NULL-via-wrapper picoquic_add_to_stream
is DOCUMENTED at picoquic.h:1500 to "erase the app_stream_ctx value"
-- changing it would be a documented-behaviour change. Pull-model
callers should use mark_active_stream anyway.

In-tree callers audited:
  - h3zero_common.c:1225 -- non-NULL ctx, unchanged.
  - picohttp/quicperf.c:764, 944 -- non-NULL ctx, unchanged.
  - picohttp/quicperf.c:1000 -- NULL with is_active=0 as explicit
    "deactivate-and-clear-ctx" before delete. After this patch ctx
    is preserved, leaving a dangling pointer to the
    quicperf_stream_ctx_t that's about to be freed. Upstream PR
    should bundle a quicperf update to call
    picoquic_unlink_app_stream_ctx alongside. Not changed here
    (aiopquic doesn't ship quicperf at runtime; only test binaries).
---
diff --git a/picoquic/sender.c b/picoquic/sender.c
index 766e7ce0..21bddb80 100644
--- a/picoquic/sender.c
+++ b/picoquic/sender.c
@@ -155,10 +155,15 @@ int picoquic_mark_active_stream(picoquic_cnx_t* cnx,
     if (ret == 0) {
         if (is_active) {
             /* The call only fails if the stream was closed or reset */
-            if (!stream->fin_requested && 
+            if (!stream->fin_requested &&
                 (!stream->reset_requested || picoquic_check_sack_list(&stream->sack_list, 0, stream->reliable_size) == 0) &&
                 cnx->callback_fn != NULL) {
-                stream->app_stream_ctx = app_stream_ctx;
+                /* NULL means "do not change app_stream_ctx" — caller
+                 * has no opinion. Use picoquic_unlink_app_stream_ctx
+                 * to explicitly clear. */
+                if (app_stream_ctx != NULL) {
+                    stream->app_stream_ctx = app_stream_ctx;
+                }
                 if (!stream->is_active) {
                     stream->is_active = 1;
                     picoquic_reinsert_by_wake_time(cnx->quic, cnx, picoquic_get_quic_time(cnx->quic));
@@ -170,7 +175,10 @@ int picoquic_mark_active_stream(picoquic_cnx_t* cnx,
         }
         else {
             stream->is_active = 0;
-            stream->app_stream_ctx = app_stream_ctx;
+            /* See note in is_active branch. */
+            if (app_stream_ctx != NULL) {
+                stream->app_stream_ctx = app_stream_ctx;
+            }
         }
     }
 
